# Marmot Project Rules for AI Assistants

## Code Style
- C23 (c2x) standard required
- No unnecessary comments
- Use nullptr, static_assert, thread_local
- Clean, minimal code
- Format with clang-format: `make format`
- Pointer alignment: `void *ptr` (not `void* ptr`)

## Build Commands
- `make build` - debug build
- `make test` - run all tests
- `make build-asan` - build with address sanitizer
- `make clean-all` - clean everything

## File Locations
- C headers: `include/marmot/`
- C implementations: `src/core/` or `src/backends/`
- Go code: `pkg/marmot/`
- Tests: `tests/` (C) or `pkg/marmot/*_test.go` (Go)
- Scripts: `scripts/` (build.sh, test.sh)

## When Modifying
1. Update `meson.build` for new C files
2. Format code: `make format`
3. Run `make build && make test` before committing
4. Use sanitizers for memory-sensitive code: `make build-asan && make test-asan`

## Architecture
- C core for performance (BLAS/Metal/MPS)
- Go wrapper for usability (cgo bindings)
- Vtable-based backends (CPU, Metal, future: CUDA)
- Coarse-grained cgo calls (minimize overhead)

## Read First
- `.ai/DEVELOPMENT.md` - Full development guide
- `docs/BUILD_SYSTEM.md` - Build system details
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` - System architecture
